<item>
            <title>[SPARK-8603] In Windows,Not able to create a Spark context from R studio </title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-8603</link>
                <project id="12315420" key="SPARK">Spark</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;In windows ,creation of spark context fails using below code from R studio&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Sys.setenv(SPARK_HOME=&quot;C:\\spark&lt;br class=&quot;atl-forced-newline&quot; /&gt;spark-1.4.0&quot;)&lt;br/&gt;
.libPaths(c(file.path(Sys.getenv(&quot;SPARK_HOME&quot;), &quot;R&quot;, &quot;lib&quot;), .libPaths()))&lt;br/&gt;
library(SparkR)&lt;br/&gt;
sc &amp;lt;- sparkR.init(master=&quot;spark://localhost:7077&quot;, appName=&quot;SparkR&quot;)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Error: JVM is not ready after 10 seconds&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Reason: Wrong file path computed in client.R. File seperator for windows&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;&amp;quot;\&amp;quot;&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; is not respected by &quot;file.Path&quot; function by default.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>&lt;p&gt;Windows, R studio&lt;/p&gt;</environment>
